    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        Assault (V)
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        To use physical force against someone without the apparent intent to harm them.
      </Box>
    </ColorBox>
    <ColorBox>
      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2">
        This covers minor criminal uses of force, Without intent to injure. That would be Aggravated Assault, or possibly a flavor of Murder.
